    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is a 2002 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S, featuring the iconic wide-body silhouette and the 3.6L M96 flat-six powerplant. This example is equipped with a precise 6-speed manual transaxle and a viscous-coupling all-wheel-drive system. To ensure long-term reliability, the intermediate shaft (IMS) bearing has been retrofitted with a high-performance ceramic solution, and the rear main seal (RMS) was replaced concurrently. The chassis maintains its composure via a sophisticated multi-link rear suspension and Bilstein dampers, while deceleration is managed by four-piston Brembo monoblock calipers. The engine exhibits no signs of bore scoring and maintains excellent oil pressure across the rev range. This is a mechanically sorted driver-tier vehicle with sharp throttle response and tight gear synchronization, ready for the spirited driver.",
